[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    39[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe risk profile is comparable to Recipes 3.6-3.9 in clinical-safety consequence terms (a missed outbreak is community spread that grows; a false alarm that goes public erodes program credibility) but distinct in cross-organizational-scope terms (this is the only recipe in the chapter where the program operates across hospital, state, and federal boundaries with HIPAA's public-health exception as the legal authority), in regulatory-framework-breadth terms (HIPAA Privacy Rule public-health exception, state public-health statutes, CSTE notifiable-condition lists, CDC eCR Now framework, NEDSS, NORS, NHSN, NMI, NWSS, FDA traceback for foodborne, multi-state coordination), and in press-conference-readiness terms (a confirmed outbreak may reach the threshold for public communication, and the data lineage has to be defensible in front of the press). The recipe correctly addresses the elevated risk in the Public-Health-Governance, Legal-Authority-Must-Be-Explicit, Cross-Jurisdictional-Coordination, Public-Communication-Infrastructure, and Self-Monitoring framings in Why This Isn't Production-Ready.[K
