[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    398[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies case-detail PHI store separation as a privacy-by-design requirement that's easy to skip and hard to retrofit. Step 1's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mingest_encounter[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m correctly establishes the pseudonymization-at-ingest pattern. Step 8 names a [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mLineListService[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and a [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpersist_line_list[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m function, suggesting the case-detail store is conceptually separate.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    399[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    400[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mBut the architectural separation is not surfaced in the General Architecture Pattern as a first-class concern. The pseudocode references a LineListService but doesn't show its access control discipline (who can call it, with what authority, with what audit trail), and the cluster's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mline_list_pointer[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m is just a pointer field without the access-discipline metadata that distinguishes "internal investigator access under specific authority" from "any role with cluster-state read access can resolve the pointer."[K
