[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    601[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPattern: A1 (cluster-grouping and outcome-event idempotency) is the now-recurring trigger-idempotency finding, surfacing for the fifteenth consecutive recipe (2.4-2.10 and 3.1-3.9).[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Same fix template (deterministic event-key derivation, conditional-write enforcement at the orchestration layer), different specific event sources (score events from the detector bank plus investigator-action events from the surveillance UI back end here). For Recipe 3.10 the consequence is calibrated to four pathways: the supervised-retraining pathway (doubled positive-class label rows distort training distribution, especially for the rarest positive class in any chapter-3 recipe), the cluster-management pathway (duplicate clusters for the same geography-syndrome pair fragment investigations and inflate the queue), the notifiable-condition reporting pathway (a redelivered confirmed-outbreak outcome event can initiate the NEDSS or NORS reporting clock twice with potentially-different start times, complicating statutory-compliance defense), and the cross-jurisdictional notification pathway (duplicate notifications sent to neighboring jurisdictions degrade trust in the federation pattern). The code review's Finding 1 has already identified the related correctness gap at the Python-companion level ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfind_existing_open_cluster[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m scan without pagination). With this finding now flagged across fifteen consecutive recipes, the per-recipe-edit posture is producing diminishing returns. The cookbook editor should treat the trigger-idempotency appendix as the highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    602[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    603[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPattern: A2 (DLQ / poison-message handling) is operationally critical for Recipe 3.10 specifically because the system feeds public-health investigations, eCR/NEDSS/NORS/NHSN/NMI external-reporting clocks, cross-jurisdictional notifications, and (when warranted) public-health-advisory issuance.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m A dropped event in the encounter-ingest path is a missed access pattern; a dropped event in the syndrome-classifier path is a missed cell-counter increment; a dropped event in the cluster-builder path is a missed cluster that never enters the surveillance queue; a dropped event in the outcome-capture path is a missed eCR/NEDSS reporting-clock initiation. For the statutory-compliance and program-credibility posture, silently-dropped events are evidentiary gaps. The DLQ-depth alarm threshold for the encounter-ingest, lab-ingest, syndrome-classifier, baseline-computer, cluster-builder, and outcome-capture paths should be 1 (single-event sensitivity).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    604[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    605[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPattern: A3 (multi-source fusion architectural primitive), A5 (suppression-rule schema and expiry-and-review workflow), A6 (case-detail PHI store separation enforcement) are all prose-vs-pseudocode asymmetries on highly-emphasized prose disciplines.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The Honest Take is unusually direct about multi-source fusion as the headline value-add ("Multi-source fusion is the biggest leverage point I've seen in the last decade"); the Why-This-Isn't-Production-Ready section names suppression-rule lifecycle management and case-detail PHI store separation as first-class concerns; the pseudocode does not architecturally enforce any of the three. A reader implementing from the pseudocode produces a system that exhibits exactly the failure modes the prose warns against (concordance never fires; suppression rules accumulate without governance; case-detail PHI is not separated from analytic pipeline). The prose-vs-pseudocode-asymmetry signature in Recipe 3.10 is comparable to Recipe 3.8's and Recipe 3.9's, which reflects the recipe's substantive engagement with operational realities but also reveals the editorial gap. The code review's Finding 3 documents the multi-source-fusion gap at the Python-companion level; the expert-review A3 documents it at the architectural level.[K
